{"title":"Pro Log: Tro-Bro Léon, La Vuelta Femenina and the Giro d’Italia","link":"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/pro-cycling-2024-vuelta-femenina","date":1715100690000,"content":"<p><a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk\">Cyclist</a><br />\n<a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/pro-cycling-2024-vuelta-femenina\">Pro Log: Tro-Bro Léon, La Vuelta Femenina and the Giro d’Italia</a></p>\n\n<p>Welcome back to another edition of <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/tags/pro-log\" target=\"_blank\">Pro Log.</a></p>\n\n\n\n<p>The <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/tags/giro-ditalia\" target=\"_blank\">Giro d’Italia</a> is underway, with Jonathan Milan (Lidl-Trek) having just won Stage 4 and Tadej Pogačar still leading the general classification. But there’s plenty of other racing to talk about, including Tro-Bro Léon and <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/vuelta-femenina-2024-gallery\" target=\"_blank\">La Vuelta Femenina</a>.</p>\n\n\n<div>\r\n                <div>\r\n                   <div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <h4><span>Related Posts</span></h4>\r\n                      </div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <div>\r\n                            <div>\r\n                            <article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/vuelta-femenina-2024-gallery\">The best photos from La Vuelta Femenina 2024: The empire strikes back</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/monument-cycling-tv-announcement\">Monument Cycling TV launches new streaming service for ‘the best of British bike racing’</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/ralph-denk-bora-hansgrohe\">Feeling bullish: Bora-Hansgrohe boss Ralph Denk profile</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/giro-ditalia-watch-live-stages-route-riders-teams-start-list\">Giro d’Italia 2024: Route, how to watch, start list and everything you need to know</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article></div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <span></span><span></span><span></span>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <div>\r\n                                                <div></div>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <div>\r\n                                                <div></div>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div>\r\n                                <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div>\r\n                                \r\n                            </div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        </div>\n\n\n<h2>Arnaud De Lie wins at Tro-Bro Léon, 5th May 2024</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/Arnaud-De-Lie-wins-Tro-Bro-Leon--970x647.jpeg\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/Arnaud-De-Lie-wins-Tro-Bro-Leon--970x646.jpeg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/Arnaud-De-Lie-wins-Tro-Bro-Leon--300x200.jpeg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/Arnaud-De-Lie-wins-Tro-Bro-Leon--768x512.jpeg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/Arnaud-De-Lie-wins-Tro-Bro-Leon--1536x1024.jpeg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/Arnaud-De-Lie-wins-Tro-Bro-Leon--2048x1365.jpeg 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/Arnaud-De-Lie-wins-Tro-Bro-Leon--750x500.jpeg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/Arnaud-De-Lie-wins-Tro-Bro-Leon--1140x760.jpeg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/Arnaud-De-Lie-wins-Tro-Bro-Leon--465x310.jpeg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/Arnaud-De-Lie-wins-Tro-Bro-Leon--620x413.jpeg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/Arnaud-De-Lie-wins-Tro-Bro-Leon--350x233.jpeg 350w\" /><figcaption>Tro Bro Leon</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Arnaud De Lie (Lotto-Dstny) won Tro-Bro Léon after an attack launched in the final 7km. The race, in its 40th edition, is famous for traversing gravel/dirt roads or <em>ribinoù</em> around Brittany. De Lie faced two flat tyres in the race and held off a chasing group determined to track him down.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The Belgian finished second last year behind Israel-Premier Tech’s Giacomo Nizzolo. He was forced to end his spring Classics campaign early this season after being diagnosed with Lyme disease, and his first win back came at the Famenne Ardenne Classic last week.</p>\n\n\n\n<div><blockquote><p><img src=\"https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/14.0.0/72x72/1f437.png\" alt=\"🐷\" /> Le petit cochon du meilleur breton revient à Mathis Le Berre !<br /><br /><img src=\"https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/14.0.0/72x72/1f437.png\" alt=\"🐷\" /> The best Breton rider of 2024 is Mathis Le Berre who receives his little piglet on the podium. <a href=\"https://twitter.com/hashtag/TroBroLeon?src=hash&amp;ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\" target=\"_blank\">#TroBroLeon</a> <a href=\"https://t.co/dAy2fA5tou\" target=\"_blank\">pic.twitter.com/dAy2fA5tou</a></p>— TRO BRO LEON (@trobroleon) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/trobroleon/status/1787161963128049853?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\" target=\"_blank\">May 5, 2024</a></blockquote> </div>\n\n\n\n<p>As always in Tro-Bro Léon, the best placed Breton won the prize of a live piglet. This year, it went to Mathias Le Berre (Arkéa-B&amp;B Hotels) who is from Saint-Brieuc, Brittany.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Organisers also promised one for De Lie.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Demi Vollering victorious at La Vuelta Femenina, 5th May 2024</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/vollering-bike-in-air-sprintcycling-970x647.jpg\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/vollering-bike-in-air-sprintcycling-970x646.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/vollering-bike-in-air-sprintcycling-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/vollering-bike-in-air-sprintcycling-768x512.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/vollering-bike-in-air-sprintcycling-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/vollering-bike-in-air-sprintcycling-2048x1366.jpg 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/vollering-bike-in-air-sprintcycling-750x500.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/vollering-bike-in-air-sprintcycling-1140x760.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/vollering-bike-in-air-sprintcycling-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/vollering-bike-in-air-sprintcycling-620x413.jpg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/vollering-bike-in-air-sprintcycling-350x233.jpg 350w\" /><figcaption>A.S.O/Sprint Cycling Agency</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Demi Vollering won La Vuelta Femenina ahead of Riejanne Markus (Visma-Lease a Bike) and Elisa Longo Borghini. After an incredible 2023, Vollering had yet to win this season going into the race.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>That changed on Stage 5, which finished atop the Category 2 Jaca; she rode clear to win by almost half a minute. The Dutch star then finished with a dramatic flourish on the last day, soloing away from her competitors to again win by almost half a minute.</p>\n\n\n\n<div><blockquote><p>𝙒𝙝𝙖𝙩 𝙖 𝙨𝙩𝙖𝙜𝙚 𝙬𝙞𝙣! <img src=\"https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/14.0.0/72x72/1f3c6.png\" alt=\"🏆\" /><br /><br /><img src=\"https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/14.0.0/72x72/1f1e8-1f1e6.png\" alt=\"🇨🇦\" /> Alison Jackson with a powerful sprint to win Stage 2 of La Vuelta Femenina <img src=\"https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/14.0.0/72x72/1f525.png\" alt=\"🔥\" /><a href=\"https://twitter.com/EF_Cannondale?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\" target=\"_blank\">@EF_Cannondale</a> | <a href=\"https://twitter.com/hashtag/LaVuelta24?src=hash&amp;ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\" target=\"_blank\">#LaVuelta24</a> | <a href=\"https://twitter.com/hashtag/LaVueltaFem?src=hash&amp;ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\" target=\"_blank\">#LaVueltaFem</a> <a href=\"https://t.co/E81Q8qaLEC\" target=\"_blank\">pic.twitter.com/E81Q8qaLEC</a></p>— Eurosport (@eurosport) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/eurosport/status/1784966191724822627?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\" target=\"_blank\">April 29, 2024</a></blockquote> </div>\n\n\n\n<p>There were plenty of memorable moments in the race aside from the general classification, including Alison Jackson’s classically joyous celebrations after winning Stage 2 with a powerful sprint.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The legendary Marianne Vos also enjoyed sprint success at La Vuelta Femenina. She won a tight finish against Charlotte Kool (DSM-Firmenich-PostNL) on Stage 3 as well as an uphill sprint on Stage 7, when she powered away from Kristen Faulkner (EF Education-Cannondale) and Longo Borghini for her 253rd career victory.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Pogačar in pink at the Giro d’Italia, 7th May 2024</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/Tadej-Pogacar-in-pink-at-the-Giro-dItalia-970x647.jpeg\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/Tadej-Pogacar-in-pink-at-the-Giro-dItalia-970x646.jpeg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/Tadej-Pogacar-in-pink-at-the-Giro-dItalia-300x200.jpeg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/Tadej-Pogacar-in-pink-at-the-Giro-dItalia-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/Tadej-Pogacar-in-pink-at-the-Giro-dItalia-1536x1024.jpeg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/Tadej-Pogacar-in-pink-at-the-Giro-dItalia-2048x1366.jpeg 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/Tadej-Pogacar-in-pink-at-the-Giro-dItalia-750x500.jpeg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/Tadej-Pogacar-in-pink-at-the-Giro-dItalia-1140x760.jpeg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/Tadej-Pogacar-in-pink-at-the-Giro-dItalia-465x310.jpeg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/Tadej-Pogacar-in-pink-at-the-Giro-dItalia-620x413.jpeg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/05/Tadej-Pogacar-in-pink-at-the-Giro-dItalia-350x233.jpeg 350w\" /><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The Giro d’Italia is ongoing with Tadej Pogačar still wearing the <em><a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/giro-d-italia-why-jersey-pink\" target=\"_blank\">maglia rosa</a>, </em>which he has had since Stage 2.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>After just missing out to Jhonatan Narváez (Ineos Grenadiers) on Stage 1, Pogačar mirrored Marco Pantani on his way to victory on Stage 2. In 1999, Pantani faced a mechanical prior to the Oropa climb before battling back to win the day. Pogačar suffered a flat tyre and hit the ground just before the ascent, and like Pantani he fought back to the bunch before passing everyone to win the stage by 27 seconds.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>If that wasn’t enough, despite Stage 3 being a sprint day, Pogačar attacked again with a couple of kilometres to go. Geraint Thomas managed to get on his wheel and the pair did their best to stay ahead of the chasing pack but were caught with 200m to go before the line. Soudal-QuickStep’s Tim Merlier went on to win the sprint.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Stage 4 was another sprint stage, this time won by Lidl-Trek’s Jonathan Milan. The stage was a nightmare for <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/biniam-girmay-profile\" target=\"_blank\">Biniam Girmay</a> (Intermarché-Wanty), however, who crashed twice in close succession and was forced to abandon the race.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>At the end of the stage, Pogačar remains at the top of the GC standings by 46 seconds ahead of Thomas.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>See you next week.</p>\n\n\n<div>\r\n                <div>\r\n                   <div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <h4><span>Related Posts</span></h4>\r\n                      </div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <div>\r\n                            <div>\r\n                            <article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/vuelta-femenina-2024-gallery\">The best photos from La Vuelta Femenina 2024: The empire strikes back</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/monument-cycling-tv-announcement\">Monument Cycling TV launches new streaming service for ‘the best of British bike racing’</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/ralph-denk-bora-hansgrohe\">Feeling bullish: Bora-Hansgrohe boss Ralph Denk profile</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/giro-ditalia-watch-live-stages-route-riders-teams-start-list\">Giro d’Italia 2024: Route, how to watch, start list and everything you need to know</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article></div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n       